

### Create a service request (client: USER or ARTISAN role)
POST http://localhost:3002/booking/request
Authorization: Bearer <CLIENT_BEARER_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Light Problem",
    "category": "Electrician",
    "description": "I need a good Electrician to fix my house Light",
    "location": "Kigo Road, Kaduna",
    "budget": 3000,
    "preferredSkills": ["Electrical", "Wiring"],
    "urgency": "URGENT",
    "contactInfo": "+2348123456789"
}

###

### Get the current client's own service requests (paginated, optional status filter)
GET http://localhost:3002/booking/requests?status=OPEN&page=1
Authorization: Bearer <CLIENT_BEARER_TOKEN>

###

### Get available service requests for an artisan (requires ARTISAN role + APPROVED status)
GET http://localhost:3002/booking/requests/available
Authorization: Bearer <ARTISAN_BEARER_TOKEN>

###

### Artisan accepts a service request
POST http://localhost:3002/booking/request/<REQUEST_UUID>/accept
Authorization: Bearer <ARTISAN_BEARER_TOKEN>
